interfaces.label: ChartColorConfiguration
description: Information about the structure of a chart to determine the color of a series within it.

children.label: totalSeries
description: Overall number of series in the current chart

children.label: maxDepth
description: Max nesting depth of the series tree

children.label: behindText
description:
Flag whether the color will be used behind text. The palette can use this information to
adjust colors for better a11y. Might be ignored depending on the palette.

children.label: syncColors
description:
Flag whether a color assignment to a given key should be remembered and re-used the next time the key shows up.
This setting might be ignored based on the palette.

interfaces.label: ColorMappingProps

children.label: model

children.label: palettes
description: A map of paletteId and palette configuration

children.label: data
description: A data description of what needs to be colored
signature: { type: "categories"; categories: (string | string[])[]; } | { type: "ranges"; min: number; max: number; bins: number; }

children.label: isDarkMode
description: Theme dark mode

children.label: specialTokens
description: A map between original and formatted tokens used to handle special cases, like the Other bucket and the empty bucket

children.label: onModelUpdate
description: A function called at every change in the model

interfaces.label: PaletteDefinition
description:
Definition of a global palette.

A palette controls the appearance of Lens charts on an editor level.
The palette wont get reset when switching charts.

A palette can hold internal state (e.g. for customizations) and also includes
an editor component to edit the internal state.

children.label: id
description: Unique id of the palette (this will be persisted along with the visualization state)

children.label: title
description: User facing title (should be i18n-ized)

children.label: internal
description: Flag indicating whether users should be able to pick this palette manually.

children.label: toExpression
description:
Serialize the internal state of the palette into an expression function.
This function should be used to pass the palette to the expression function applying color and other styles

children.label: state
description: The internal state of the palette

children.label: getCategoricalColor
description: Color a series according to the internal rules of the palette.
signature: | undefined, state?: T | undefined) => string | null

children.label: series
description: The current series along with its ancestors.

children.label: state
description: The internal state of the palette

children.label: getCategoricalColors
description:
Get a spectrum of colors of the current palette.
This can be used if the chart wants to control color assignment locally.

children.label: canDynamicColoring
description: Define whether a palette supports dynamic coloring (i.e. gradient colors mapped to number values)

children.label: getColorForValue
description:
Get the assigned color for the given value based on its data domain and state settings.
This can be used for dynamic coloring based on uniform color distribution or custom stops.
signature: ((value: number | undefined, state: T, { min, max }: { min: number; max: number; }) => string | undefined) | undefined

interfaces.label: SeriesLayer
description:
Information about a series in a chart used to determine its color.
Series layers can be nested, this means each series layer can have an ancestor.

children.label: name
description: Name of the series (can be used for lookup-based coloring)

children.label: rankAtDepth
description: Rank of the series compared to siblings with the same ancestor

children.label: totalSeriesAtDepth
description: Total number of series with the same ancestor
